<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   North's Pomminnyon Supports Overseas Proposal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1501113494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1038 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1501113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 15 (KCNA) -- The North side 
headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's 
Reunification (Pomminnyon) declared it would positively 
contribute to the achievement of great national unity and the 
noble cause of the country's reunification, keeping pace with 
the patriotic movement of Koreans in the South and overseas for 
great national unity. 
  In a statement released today, the Central Committee of the 
North side headquarters of Pomminnyon highly estimates and fully 
supports a proposal and call of the overseas Koreans' 
headquarters of Pomminnyon for setting this as a "year of great 
national unity" for national reunification. 
  Noting that the proposal and call are very just and timely 
both in view of the nature of the national reunification 
question and the desire of the fellow countrymen for great 
national unity and they will help convincingly promote the 
reunification in the `90s, the statement says: 
  "The North side headquarters, in hearty response to the 
proposal of the overseas Koreans' headquarters, will vigorously 
struggle shoulder to shoulder with Koreans overseas to achieve 
great unity of the nation this year. 
  "Regarding the Kim Yong-sam group as the foe of great 
national unity, it will staunchly struggle against it and, in 
this way, actively promote great national unity with Koreans in 
the South and overseas. 
  "We hold that anybody must refrain from rejecting 
Pomminnyon, 
a pan-national umbrella organization for great national unity 
and the reunification of the country, and join in the patriotic 
movement for reunification." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

