<H3> <TI>   Toyota To Increase U.S. Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2101012994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0055 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2101012994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 21 KYODO -- Toyota Motor Corp. expects 
its U.S. manufacturing arm to produce some 300,000 units this 
year, an increase of about 25 percent over the previous year, a 
company spokesman said Friday [21 January]. 
  Toyota Motor Manufacturing U.S.A. Inc. (TMM), based in 
Georgetown, Kentucky, turned out 234,000 units last year, the 
spokesman said. 
  TMM is scheduled to begin production at a second plant next 
to the current facility in late March. 
  The new plant will assemble the Camry, which is now built at 
the current plant, and the Avalon, TMM's new flagship car to be 
introduced this autumn. 
  Besides Camry sedans, the current Georgetown facility also 
produces and exports Camry station wagons and coupes to several 
foreign countries, including Japan. 

</TEXT>

