  [Text] Seoul, Jan. 20 KYODO -- U.S. Central Intelligence 
Agency (CIA) Director James Woolsey has made an unpublicized 
visit to Seoul for talks with South Korean President Kim 
Yong-sam and Defense Minister Yi Byong-tae, a South Korean daily 
reported Thursday [20 January]. 
  The HANGYORE SHINMUN said Woolsey flew into Seoul in secrecy 
on Tuesday to discuss the Korean situation amid international 
efforts to persuade North Korea to "abandon its nuclear program." 
