<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   EPA Says Industrial Production Still Sluggish </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1801100494 Tokyo KYODO in English 0926 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1801100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 18 KYODO -- Japan's industrial 
production remains sluggish so far in January, except in limited 
sectors including the semiconductor industry, the Economic 
Planning Agency (EPA) said in a survey published Tuesday [18 
January]. 
  It also said efforts to reduce inventories were making 
little 
progress. 
  Domestic shipments of videocassette recorders, refrigerators 
and washing machines in January recorded year-on-year increases, 
however. 
  In the nonmanufacturing sector, the value of lease contracts 
continues to decrease and domestic freight transport business, 
other than home delivery of parcels, remains slow, the EPA said. 

</TEXT>

