<H3> <TI>   Hosokawa Calls Stable Employment `Top Priority' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2101040094 Tokyo KYODO in English 1242 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2101040094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 21 KYODO -- Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa said Friday [21 January] that ensuring a stable 
employment environment is one of the top priority jobs for the 
government. 
  Hosokawa told the second meeting of a special cabinet forum 
on employment that the government needs to put into practice as 
early as possible a program of creating more jobs that was 
worked out in mid-December by the Labor Ministry. 
  Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii, also present at the 
meeting, 
pledged fiscal support for the program, while Minister of 
International Trade and Industry Hiroshi Kumagai said his 
ministry plans to nurture promising industries such as 
biotechnology, new energy and information to create new jobs. 
  Labor Minister Chikara Sakaguchi, meanwhile, called for an 
early drafting of a new economic pump-primer by the government, 
saying improvement in the labor climate needs recovery of the 
economy. 

</TEXT>

