<H3> <TI>   NTT To Enter U.S. Telecommunications Market </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2101044394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1233 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2101044394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New York, Jan. 20 KYODO -- Japan's domestic 
telecommunications giant, Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp., 
said Thursday [20 January] it has paved the way for entry into 
the U.S. telecommunications market. 
  The former government-run monopoly said a contract was 
signed 
with U.S. mobile telecom firm Nextel Communications Inc. (CALL) 
on Thursday to form a partnership between the two companies. 
  Under the agreement, NTT will acquire a 0.9% stake 
in the 
U.S. partner for 75 million dollars and cooperate in the 
deployment of Nextel's digital mobile networks throughout the 
United States, the company said. 
  NTT is promoting in Japan its own digital communications 
service, known as integrated service digital network. 
  Besides NTT, Motorola Inc. of the United States and 
Matsushita Communication Industrial Co., an affiliate of 
consumer electronics maker Matsushita Electric Industrial Co., 
have invested in Nextel. 

</TEXT>

