<H3> <TI>   Le Duc Anh Receives Iranian Minister. </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1901152394 Hanoi VNA in English 1505 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1901152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan. 19 -- President Le Duc Anh today 
received Mr. Issa Kalantari, minister of agriculture of the 
Islamic Republic of Iran who is here for a visit to Vietnam. 
  During the reception, Mr. Isa Kalantari expressed his 
pleasure at his first visit to Vietnam and his sincere thanks 
for President Le Duc Anh's reception. He also conveyed the 
Iranian President Rafsanjani's best regards to President Le Duc 
Anh and invited him to pay a visit to Iran. He introduced to 
President Le Duc Anh the Iranian people's achievements in their 
economic restoration and national reconstruction and appreciated 
the cooperation between the two countries in the fields of 
economy, especially agriculture, agricultural products 
exchanges, sciences, technology and training experts. He also 
expressed his wishes for the above-said cooperation to further 
expand and develop in various fields. 
  For his part, President Le Duc Anh welcomed Mr. Isa 
Kalantari's Vietnam visit and expressed his pleasure at the 
achievements recorded by the Iranian people. On behalf of the 
Vietnamese people President Le Duc Anh thanked the Iranian 
Government and people for their support and assistance to the 
cause of Vietnam's former national liberation and current 
national construction. He noted that Vietnam's foreign policy 
is to be friends with all countries in order to expand the 
cooperation in the interest of each country, for peace, 
stability and development in the region and in the world. He 
believed that the Iran-Vietnam cooperation in the fields of 
economy, agriculture and trade will be constantly expanded and 
developed. President asked Mr. Kalantari conveyed his best 
regards and wishes to President Rafsanjani and thanked him for 
his invitation to visit Iran and wished the Iranian people 
prosperous and happy [sentence as received]. 

</TEXT>

