<F P=102>  BK2101143194 Hanoi VNA in English 1422 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2101143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Jan. 21 -- Malaysian National News Agency 
(BERNAMA) held a ceremony this evening to inaugurate its bureau 
here. 
  Among those present at the event were Vice Foreign Minister 
Le Mai, General Director of VIETNAM NEWS AGENCY Do Phuong, 
Editor-in-Chief of the daily NHAN DAN newspaper Huu Tho, General 
Director of Vietnam Television Ho Anh Dung and other Vietnamese 
officials. On the Malaysian side were Editor-in-Chief of 
BERNAMA Abdul Rahman Sulaiman and Ambassador to Vietnam Cheah 
Sam Kip. 
  Addressing the ceremony, Mr. Sulaiman thanked Vietnamese 
concerned offices for their assistance to BERNAMA to open its 
bureau in Hanoi, which, he said, constitutes an opportunity to 
contribute to the strengthening of mutual understanding between 
the two countries for the sake of peace, stability and 
development in the region. 
  In his turn, Vice Foreign Minister Le Mai noted that in 
recent years, the relations of friendship and cooperation 
between Vietnam and Malaysia had constantly developed. The 
opening of a BERNAMA bureau in Hanoi is a vivid manifestation of 
the said relations, he added. Mr Mai further said Vietnamese 
side would create favourable conditions for BERNAMA to perform 
its professional activities in order to further consolidate the 
fine relations between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

