<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Doan Khue Greets Counterpart on LPA Anniversary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2001143394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2330 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2001143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the occasion of 45th founding anniversary of the 
Lao People's Army [LPA] (20 January 1949-94), General Doan Khue, 
minister of National Defense, sent a greeting message to Senior 
Lieutenant General Choummali Sai-ngason, defense minister of the 
Lao People's Democratic Republic. The message reads: 
  Dear comrade minister; on the occasion of the 45th founding 
anniversary of the LPA, on behalf of all cadres and combatants 
of the Vietnam People's Army and on my behalf, I would like to 
convey to you, and through you to all the cadres and combatants 
of the fraternal LPA, my most sincere greetings of solidarity. 
  Throughout the last 45 years, under the leadership of the 
Lao 
People's Revolutionary Party [LPRP], the LPA and the multiethnic 
Lao people have bravely advanced through all difficulties and 
obstacles, continously defeated all the invading imperialists as 
well as the domestic reactionaries, achieved glorious victories, 
and restored independence and freedom to the fatherland. 
  After the complete liberation of the country, the Lao armed 
forces still went on to crush all the dark schemes and sabotage 
activities of the enemies. In the past 20 year, the Lao 
People's Democratic Republic have recorded important 
achievements in all areas of national security, politics, and 
external relations, and in the socioeconomic domain. Domestic 
stability is constantly improving, the country's status on the 
international stage is being heightened, thus contributing to 
the protection of peace and stability in Southeast Asia as well 
as in the world. 
  We are happy for your achievements, and strongly trust that 
the Lao people and the LPA will continue to record ever greater 
achievements, successfully implement the resolution of the Fifth 
Congress of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party, and build a 
peaceful, independent, unified, and prosperous Laos. 
  Also on this occasion, on behalf of the Vietnam People's 
Army, I would like to express my sincere gratitude to the LPRP, 
the government, the people, and the LPA, for the fine sentiments 
and valuable assistance they had given to the Vietnamese people 
and the people's army during the past revolution as well as in 
the present rennovation undertaking. 
  May the special friendly solidarity and the comprehensive 
cooperation between the two peoples and the two armies of 
Vietnam and Laos be evermore solidified and developed. I wish 
you, comrade minister, good health and happiness in your life, 
and more achievements in fulfilling your noble duties. 
  My solemn salute to you, dear comrade. 

</TEXT>

