<H3> <TI>   Party Reports 1993 Enrollment Figures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2001092794 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
0500 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2001092794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last year party development work was carried out 
fairly well nationwide. According to incomplete reports, party 
organizations admitted nearly 50,000 new members, 30 percent 
more than the 1992 figure. 
  Among the departments under the Central Committee, the Army 
party organizations had the most new members admitted. The 
number of young people joining the party who had been members of 
the Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Federation was also 
significantly large, comprising about 50 percent of the total. 
The number of new members with high levels of education was 
also large, and the numbers of women and ethnic minorities also 
were higher than before. 

</TEXT>

