<H3> <TI>   North Asks To Send Condolence Team for Mun </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2001035094 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0320 GMT 20 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2001035094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paek In-chun, chairman of North Korea's National 
Alliance for the Country's Reunification [Pomminnyon], sent a 
telephone message to Deputy Prime Minister and Unification 
Minister Yi Yong-tok today. He revealed in the telephone 
message that North Korea would send a condolence team on the 
death of Rev. Mun Ik-hwan and proposed that a working-level 
contact be held tomorrow to discuss the issue of sending a 
condolence team to Seoul. 
  Referring to the mounting affection and sympathy of the 
North 
Korean people for Rev. Mun Ik-hwan who died without seeing the 
realization of reunification for which he worked throughout his 
life, Paek In-chun said that North Korea would send a condolence 
team to Seoul. Paek In-chun then proposed that a working-level 
contact be held in Panmunjom tomorrow morning to discuss this 
issue. 

</TEXT>

