<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Group Not Allowed at Bier </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2001085494 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0805 GMT 20 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2001085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today North Korea proposed in a telephone message 
that it would send a condolence team of the National Alliance 
for the Country's Reunification [Pomminnyon] to the bier of the 
late Rev. Mun Ik-hwan, but the government has decided not to 
accept it. 
  National Unification Board spokesman Kim Hyong-ki said in a 
commentary issued this afternoon that because Pomminnyon is 
defined as an organization benefiting the enemy in accordance 
with a final ruling made by the Supreme Court in 1992, and 
because of the aggravated situation between North and South 
Korea caused by the North Korean nuclear issue, North Korea's 
proposal would not be helpful to improving North-South relations 
at all. According to this judgment, the government has decided 
to refuse the proposal. 

</TEXT>

