<H3> <TI>   DP Supports Businessmen's Visit to DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1401092494 Seoul HANGUK ILBO in Korean 14 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK1401092494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul HANGUK ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 13 January, the Democratic Party [DP] held a 
policy seminar at the hall of lawmakers. This seminar entitled 
"The Prospect for the North Korean Nuclear Issue and North-South 
Relations" was sponsored by the party policy committee. 
  In the seminar, lawmaker Pak Sil said that "because there is 
a possible breakthrough in the settlement of the nuclear issue 
as a result of North Korea's acceptance of the nuclear 
inspection by the International Atomic Energy Agency, the 
government must allow businessmen to visit North Korea." 
  He predicted that "because this year is the year in which 
there is no election in South Korea, in which the Kim Yong-sam 
government can strengthen its power, and in which North Korea 
can consolidate the transfer of power from Kim Il-song to his 
son, it is possible for the North and South to create conditions 
for the North-South summit talks." 

