<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Assurance on DPRK-Bound Submarines </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2101090394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0807 GMT 21 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2101090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The submarines which Russia has sold to North Korea 
recently were confirmed to be decommissioned submarines without 
any strategic value. 
  A relevant Foreign Ministry official revealed that the 
Russian Government informed our government that the submarines 
that Russia recently sold to North Korea were decommissioned 
submarines from which weapons and equipment were all removed. 
Therefore, these submarines were sold in accordance with a 
commercial contract, not a contract for weapons supply, and this 
contract prescribed that the Russian side will inspect the work 
of dismantling the decommissioned submarines. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

