<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Requests Repaying Loan With Weapons </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2101063494 Seoul YONHAP in English 0627 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2101063494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Jan. 21 (YONHAP) -- Russia has made official 
its offer to repay a South Korean loan with military hardware 
and technology, Foreign Ministry officials said Friday. 
  The Ministry had received a list, very close to one sent 
last 
month by a private defense institute, of arms and equipment that 
it was willing to include in such a deal on Jan. 19, they said. 
  To make the offer formal, Deputy Premier Aleksandr Shokhin 
sent a signed letter with it, they said. 
  Talks are expected among Foreign, Defense and Finance 
Ministry officials to decide whether Russian arms are compatible 
with Korea's current weapons and to weigh the pluses of Moscow's 
proposal. 
  Seoul agreed on 3 billion U.S. dollars in aid to Moscow but 
delivered only 1.47 billion dollars and suspended the rest after 
the collapse of the Soviet Union. 
  When Shokhin was visiting the Taejon Expo last year, he 
suggested that his country pay back the loan in military goods. 

</TEXT>

