<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] A Western source in Beijing said on 19 January that 
Kim Chong-u, vice chairman of North Korea's External Economic 
Committee, who had been scheduled to visit China sometime this 
week, postponed the visit without a prior notice and that this 
has perplexed the Chinese side. 
  This source also said: The Chinese side faxed a message to 
North Korea's External Economic Committee and asked why he 
postponed the visit and when he would visit. However, the North 
Korean has not made a reply. 
  Kim was scheduled to visit China and discuss the 
construction 
of a road between the Najin-Sonbong area and Chongjin and other 
ways to promote cooperation for the Tumen River project. 

