<H3> <TI>   Amount of PRC Military Aid to DPRK Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2101015094 Seoul SEOUL SINMUN in Korean 21 Jan 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> SK2101015094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul SEOUL SINMUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] According to a Chinese source on 20 January, China 
has given North Korea at least 7.5 billion won a year in 
military aid, even after the reduction of its aid to North Korea 
a few years ago. 
  This source, well versed in North Korean affairs, said that 
he "had recently heard this directly from a senior official of 
the Chinese Government," and said, "the details of the Chinese 
military aid to North Korea are not known. It has been learned, 
however, that the night infrared detection equipment is one of 
the items provided by China to North Korea." 
  The source also said that in addition to the military aid, 
China has annually provided North Korea with large-scale 
assistance of energy, including oil and coal; and of food 
including beans, corn, and rice, and that the annual food 
assistance reached about 15 billion won. 

</TEXT>

