<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Reports Increase in Reserves </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1801094494 Kuala Lumpur NEW STRAITS TIMES in English 17 
Jan 94 p 20 </F>

<F P=103> BK1801094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur NEW STRAITS TIMES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bank Negara's gold and foreign exchange and other 
reserves, including special drawing rights rose to RM [Malaysian 
ringgit] 64,930.89 million as at Dec 15, 1993, from RM 60,265.32 
million a forthnight earlier. 
  A statement from the central bank said its total assets and 
liabilities also increased to RM 93,788.00 million from RM 
92,727.63 million previously. 
  Loans and advances rose to RM 2,366.83 million from RM 
2,351.96 million while holdings of Malaysian Government papers, 
declined to RM 377.83 million from RM 515.78 million. 
  Holdings of bills discounted fell to RM 3,644.97 million 
against RM 3,695.66 million previously. 
  Currency in circulation also dropped to RM 14,032.54 million 
from the previous figure of RM 14,099.11 million. 
  Deposits of commercial banks, finance companies and merchant 
banks totalled RM 49,200.81 million as at Dec 15 against RM 
47,780.51 million. 
  Deposits of Federal Government declined to RM 5,457.06 
million from RM 5,978.51 million while State Government deposits 
increased to RM 610.50 million from RM 504.69 million a 
forthnight ago. 

</TEXT>

