<H3> <TI>   Conference on Bosnia Held in Kuala Lumpur </TI></H3>
<H4>   Bosnian President Arrives 21 Jan </H4>
<F P=102> BK2201101694 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0353 GMT 22 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2201101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, Jan 22 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- President 
Alija Izetbegovic arrived here Friday with a 12-member 
delegation for a four-day working visit. 
  On hand to receive the Bosnian leeder at the Kuala Lumpur 
International Airport were Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad 
Badawi, Law Minister Syed Hamid Albar, who is the 
minister-in-attendance, chairman of the Malaysia Parliamentary 
Committee on Bosnia- Herzegovina (MPC-BH) Dominic Puthucheary, 
and other officials. 
  President Alija, whose delegation includes Foreign Minister 
Dr. Irfan Ljubijankic, is scheduled to address the international 
conference of parliamentarians on Bosnia-Herzegovina and meet 
Prime Minister Dr. Mahathir Mohamed for talks. 
  Arriving from Geneva, President Alija became the first state 
visitor to receive the quarter-guard salute from a team of eight 
Royal Malay Regiment on arrival at the airport. 
  A Wisma Putra (Foreign Ministry) official said the ceremony 
was conducted upon recommendation by Dr. Mahathir, who picked 
the idea during his recent visit to Europe. 
  During his four-day visit, President Alija would also be 
meeting the Bosnian community here and having a dialogue with 
ambassadors from members of the Organisation of International 
Conference countries. 
  President Alija will also have an audience with the Yang 
Dipertuan Agung (King) Sultan Azlan Shah on Monday. 

</TEXT>

