<F P=102>  BK2201094594 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0407 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2201094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 22 Jan (AKP) -- A delegation from the 
Austrian Foreign Ministry led by its deputy minister, Wolfgang 
Schallenberg, arrived in Phnom Penh on Friday [21 January] for 
an official five-day visit to Cambodia. 
  The delegation was greeted at Pochentong airport by Uch 
Kim-an, state secretary for foreign affairs and international 
cooperation, and other Cambodian personalities. 
  The Austrian deputy minister will meet with Prince Norodom 
Sirivut, deputy prime minister and minister of foreign affairs 
and international cooperation, and those in charge of the 
ministries of information and industry. 
  The delegation plans to visit Angkor Wat in Siem Reap 
Province on Monday before leaving the next day for Ho Chi Minh 
City, Vietnam. 

