<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reacts to ROK Defense Ministry Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2201044594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0435 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2201044594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["War Trumpeting Inciting Confrontation" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 22 (KCNA) -- The traitor Kim 
Yong- sam, when receiving "this year's working plan" of the 
puppet Ministry of Defence on January 20, cried that "the combat 
capabilities" of the puppet Army "should be increased" to cope 
with "the provocation of the North", according to a radio report 
from Seoul. 
  The puppet defence minister there blared that "a perfect 
combat posture of the Army will be taken to deal with armed 
provocation" of the North. 
  The South Korean puppets revealed their scheme to hurt 
fellow 
countrymen with arms, shouting themselves hoarse for "the 
completion of military posture" and "an immediate retaliation" 
from the beginning of the year. This shows that they will not 
hesitate to light the fuse of war to slay fellow countrymen. It 
must not be overlooked here that the traitor, maliciously 
charging the North with its fictitious "nuclear issue" again, 
spun out the malicious trash that the North "refuses to give up 
nuclear development" because it "has not abandoned its lingering 
desire for unification through communization and unification 
with arms." 
  This is a despicable ruse of the traitor to justify armed 
provocations of his group on the pretext of the North's 
"nuclear issue". 
  Making consistent efforts for peace of the country and its 
peaceful reunification, the North put forward the 10-point 
programme of the great unity of the whole nation and a proposal 
for the exchange of special envoys to discuss and resolve 
outstanding questions between the North and the South. The 
South Korean puppets, however, are following a road of 
dependence on foreign forces and North-South confrontation, 
shunning them. 
  The Kim Yong-sam group must stop running wild, mindful of 
the 
irrevocable consequences of its reckless war racket and increase 
of tensions. 

</TEXT>

