<H3> <TI>   South Radio Cited on Student Protest of U.S. </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1901044994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0409 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1901044994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Some 700 students 
affiliated with the Seoul District Federation of General Student 
Councils (Sochongnyon) of South Korea met on January 15 and 
issued a resolution for checking rice market opening, 
Seoul-based Christian Broadcasting System reported. 
  Accusing the present regime of bowing to the U.S. pressure 
for rice import liberalization, the resolution called for 
blocking the "parliamentary ratification" of rice market opening. 
  The ralliers also denounced the authorities' opening of the 
financial market. 
  They declared they would wage a vigorous struggle against 
the 
U.S. pressure for market opening. 

</TEXT>

