<H3> <TI>   South's Handling of Water Pollution Issue Derided </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1801061994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0437 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1801061994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Water Pollution Under Corrupt Politics" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
denounces the crime of the Kim Yong-sam clique in causing the 
pollution of the Naktong river. 
  The commentary titled "water pollution under corrupt 
politics" notes that more than ten million people in Pusan and 
North and South Kyongsang Provinces of South Korea are suffering 
from a shortage of drinking water because the Naktong River is 
seriously contaminated with ammonia nitrogen and carcinogenic 
benzene, toluene and other toxic substances. 
  The news analyst says: 
  The Kim Yong-sam clique, much upset, is resorting to petty 
tricks to lull the resentment of the people, sending "a 
fact-finding team" to the spot and publishing "a message of 
apology to the people" in the name of the puppet prime minister. 
On the other hand, it is working hard to shirk the blame for 
the drinking water problem. 
  Such hide-and-seek of the puppets, however, can work on 
nobody at all. [sentence as received] 
  The South Korean people know only too well it is the Kim 
Yong-sam clique that has received thick bundles of banknotes 
from pollution-causing comprador businesses and connived at 
their dumping of toxic waste water into the Naktong River. 
  Under corrupt politics, nature and society become sick and 
degenerated. 
  With nothing can the Kim Yong-sam clique conceal its 
treacherous acts in turning South Korea into "the worst hell of 
pollution in the world" and imposing sufferings and misfortunes 
on the people. 

</TEXT>

