<F P=102>  SK1701102994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1010 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1701102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Leader Kim Chong-il, Iron-Willed Brilliant Commander" -- </F>
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, January 17 (KCNA) -- South Korean people 
are looking up to the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il as the 
lodestar of the nation and reunification. 
  A newspaper reporter in Seoul, while having a conversation 
with his colleagues about the situation, said: European and 
American big powers are conspiring with each other in putting 
pressure upon North Korea under the pretext of the fictitious 
"nuclear issue" in an attempt to stifle the socialist system of 
the North, but the North is braving it. 
  The North is demonstrating the might of the Republic 
entirely 
thanks to the outstanding guidance of the leader Kim Chong-il, 
the great statesman, he noted, adding: 
  The leader Kim Chong-il who has literary and military 
accomplishments is an iron-willed brilliant commander with firm 
faith, a distinguished great politician with correct judgment 
and outstanding leadership ability and a prominent leader of the 
international socialist movement who is guiding the movement for 
rebuilding socialism, standing in the centre of world politics. 
  A university professor in Seoul told his students: Mr. Kim 
Chong-il is a man with gifted qualification. He is not only a 
great man of learning, a great master of idea and theory but a 
master of political art who is leading people to social progress 
by applying knowledge and theory. This is eloquently proved by 
the course of dramatic changes in political, economic and 
cultural domains of the North. 
  It is good luck of our fellow countrymen to have held such a 
peerless great man as Mr. Kim Chong-il in high esteem as the 
lodestar of the nation. 
  A certain Yi in Kangso District, Seoul, told his villagers: 
I firmly believe that as Mr. Kim Chong-il looks after our 
people, the country would be reunified before long and people 
would be well off under his leadership. It is General Kim 
Il-song and Mr. Kim Chong-il who we should believe and follow. 

</TEXT>

