<DATE1>  25 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Other Media Report Address </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1901111894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1033 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1901111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- The New Year address 
of the great leader President Kim Il-song was reported by 
foreign media. 
  The Libyan paper AL JAHAF AL AHDAR carried part of his New 
Year address elucidating a solution of the nuclear issue on the 
Korean peninsula. 
  The paper noted in the preface that the nuclear issue on the 
Korean peninsula is related to the maneuvers of the United 
States. 
  Last year the U.S. and its followers, it said, led the 
situation on the Korean peninsula to the brink of war by 
inventing the "suspicion of nuclear development by North Korea" 
in an attempt to stifle Korean-style socialism centred on the 
masses. 
  However, the Korean people who have experienced the 
superiority of socialism to capitalism through their life rose 
as one to defend their choice, gains, national dignity, the 
country and its independence and countered the moves of the 
enemy by declaring withdrawal from the Nuclear Nonproliferation 
Treaty and a semi-war state, the paper pointed out, and added: 
  Their response was an unexpected, surprising blow to the 
provokers. 
  The nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula can cover be 
solved 
by means of pressure and threat. 
  The New Year address was also reported by newspapers and 
radios of India, Zambia, the Netherlands, Britain, Nepal, China, 
Burundi, Guyana, Nicaragua, Costa Rica and Yemen. 
  The Cameroonian paper LE CHEMIN carried the full text of the 
address. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

