<F P=103> SK1601085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 16 (KCNA) -- The president of the 
National Assembly of People's Power of Cuba, Ricardo Alarcon de 
Quesada, voiced full support for the policies for national 
reunification clarified by the great leader President Kim 
Il-song in his New Year address. 
  In a solidarity message to chairman of the Supreme People's 
Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea Yang 
Hyong-sop, he said the Korean people would be always fully 
supported by the Communist Party, Government and people of Cuba. 
  He expressed the belief that friendship and solidarity 
between the Cuban and Korean peoples united closely with each 
other in the common struggle against the imperialists' 
aggressive moves and for socialist construction would further 
develop with each passing day. 

</TEXT>

