<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Calls For Solidarity of `Popular Masses' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1801104994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1026 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1801104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The desire of the 
popular masses to live in a free and peaceful world, freed from 
domination and subjugation, exploitation and oppression, can be 
realized only through the cause of independence of the popular 
masses, the cause of socialism, says NODONG SINMUN in an article 
today. The article headlined "Guarantee for Moving Up Bright 
Future of Mankind" reads in part: 
  The great leader President Kim Il-song in his New Year 
address said if the progressive people of the world promote 
historical development by strengthening their unity and 
solidarity under the banner of independence against imperialism, 
they shall soon be able to shape a bright future for humanity. 
  The imperialists are now intensifying political, economic 
and 
military pressure to stifle the countries going forward under 
the banner of socialism and are intensifying their maneuverings 
to dominate and interfere in the affairs of the developing 
countries aspiring after socialism. 
  To strengthen unity and solidarity is a firm guarantee for 
the world progressive people to smash the imperialists' moves. 
It stands out with greater urgency because the imperialist 
reactionaries are becoming undisguised in their attempt to beat 
one by one the progressive countries advancing toward 
independence, sovereignty and socialism. 
  Unity and solidarity are a most powerful weapon for the 
cause 
of independence, the cause of socialism, and a decisive 
guarantee for victory. To strengthen it, it is essential to 
adhere to the principle of independence, equality and mutual 
respect. 
  It is necessary to strengthen the unity and solidarity of 
the 
revolutionary parties struggling for the victory of the cause of 
independence, the cause of socialism, of the popular masses. 
  The Pyongyang declaration serves as a banner under which 
international unity and solidarity can be strengthened in the 
struggle for socialism. 
  Independence, peace and friendship are the basic idea of the 
foreign policy of the Workers' Party of Korea and the Government 
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  The Korean people value their unity and solidarity with all 
the progressive people of the world aspiring after 
independence, sovereignty and socialism and will, in the future, 
too, give strong impetus to the trend of history by 
strengthening unity and solidarity with them. 

</TEXT>

