<H3> <TI>   Workers Vow To Step Up `March of Socialism' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1601090694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0811 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1601090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 16 (KCNA) -- Workers of workshops 
and workteams of industrial establishments and farmers of 
cooperative farms in Korea held meetings to vow to implement to 
the letter the militant tasks set forth by the great leader 
President Kim Il-song in his New Year address. 
  The speakers said that the New Year address of President Kim 
Il-song is a highly important guideline to which the Korean 
people should hold fast this year. They called for stepping up 
the general onward march of socialism in the revolutionary 
spirit of self- reliance and hard struggle by further 
strengthening the might of singlehearted unity. 
  They said that they would successfully fulfil this year's 
plans for socialist economic construction by making continued 
innovations and uninterrupted advance in the spirit of Chollima 
spurred on by the "speed of the '90s" under the militant slogan 
"Let us hasten the general march of socialism in the 
revolutionary spirit of self-reliance and fortitude". 
  They declared that they would, with unfailing loyalty to the 
party and the leader, make continued innovations and 
uninterrupted advance in the fighting spirit which was displayed 
during the rigorous war and in the same spirit and stamina with 
which they brought about a great upsurge of Chollima in the 
difficult post-war period and thus make 1994 a year of 
historical advance in the Korean revolution and construction. 

</TEXT>

