<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buddhists Hold Masses for National Reunification </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1901110894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1011 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1901110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Buddhist masses for 
national reunification were held at temples throughout the 
country today on the day of Buddha's attainment of great wisdom. 
  The masses were attended by monks of the temples, believers 
and clergymen from the Central Committee of the Korean Buddhists 
Federation and its provincial, city and county committees. 
  The preachers said that in order to realise the idea of 
"getting rid of the pain and attaining happiness," the basic 
idea of Buddhists, it was imperative to reunify the country at 
an early date. 
  They stressed that the country should be reunified in the 
form of a confederation and the best way to it was to implement 
"10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation for 
the reunification of the country" laid down by respected 
President Kim Il-song. 
  They called on all the Buddhists in the North, South and 
overseas to closely unite with each other under the banner of 
great national unity and make a tangible contribution to the 
cause of national reunification, thus achieving the 
reunification in the '90s without fail. 

</TEXT>

