<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Final Damming Project on Tideland Completed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1401151594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1502 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1401151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- The final damming 
project on the Chongsu Islet tideland was completed successfully 
in Korea in the new year. 
  The nature-remaking project is to reclaim 1,000 hectares of 
land by building a dam linking Sikyo-ri, Chongsu Islet and 
Tungam-ri in Kangyong County, South Hwanghae Province. 
  The project has increased the area of cultivated land and 
changed the coastline and looks of the country. 
  The builders of the South Hwanghae Provincial Chongdan 
General Tideland Reclamation Enterprise who were in charge of 
the project had overfulfilled the daily plan by more than 70 
percent on an average in the whole period of the project by 
boosting the utility rate of transport means and actively 
introducing new construction methods. 

