<H3> <TI>   Cement Production Said Constantly Increasing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1801044594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0410 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1801044594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- Cement production is 
on the constant increase in Korea. 
  The Sunchon cement complex produced 20,000 more tons of 
cement and the Haeju cement factory 5,600 more tons in the first 
17 days of January than in the same days last year. 
  The Sangwon cement complex is topping its daily assignments 
by 20 percent by keeping all the kilns at full-capacity 
operation. 
  The February 8 cement complex, the Chonnaeri cement factory 
and other cement producers are honoring their daily assignments 
by organizing production efficiently. 
  Production has been lifted to a high rate at more than 200 
minor cement factories in different parts of the country. 
  The Songsan, Sindok, Madong and other limestone mines, the 
Sunchon and Kangdong District coal mining complexes and other 
coal mines are supplying limestone and coal to cement factories 
in time. 

</TEXT>

