<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kumano Supports Presummit Economic Package </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2401080894 Tokyo KYODO in English 0758 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2401080894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 24 KYODO -- The government should 
compile new economic pump-priming measures before the scheduled 
Japan-U.S. summit in Washington on February 11, Japan's Vice 
Trade Minister suggested Monday [24 January]. Hideaki Kumano, 
vice minister of international trade and industry, told 
reporters that the U.S. Government should be informed of the 
contents of the economic stimulus package before the summit 
between Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa and U.S. President 
Bill Clinton. 
  Kumano said his ministry and the Finance Ministry are 
holding 
working-level talks to coordinate views on the package. The 
package is expected to include major income tax cuts and an 
expanded budget for fiscal 1994, which begins next April 1. 

</TEXT>

