Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 24 KYODO -- A high-ranking government 
source said Monday [24 January] the announcement of the planned 
economic stimulus package will be delayed to February. 
  The official, who did not want to be identified, said that 
the delay is inevitable because of political turmoil after the 
government's defeat Friday of political reform bills in the 
House of Councillors. The economic measures had been widely 
expected to be implemented in late January. 

