<F P=102>  OW2401022694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0213 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2401022694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 24 KYODO -- Finance Minister Hirohisa 
Fujii said Monday [24 January] the government will simply "wait 
and see" the stock market situation despite the tumble in 
morning trading over political turmoil. 
  Fujii attributed the sharp decline to the muddy outlook in 
the political scene ahead. But "(stock price fluctuations) are 
a common phenomenon," he said. "We will wait and see for the 
time being," he said. 
  The key Nikkei stock average of 225 selected issues plunged 
more than 4 percent during the two-hour session in a negative 
reaction to the defeat on Friday of the government's political 
reform bills in the House of Councillors. 

