<H3> <TI>   Government Troops Seize South Separatist Camp </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2301095994 Bangkok THE SUNDAY POST in English 23 Jan 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> BK2301095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THE SUNDAY POST </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] YALA -- A camp of the Barisan Revolusi Nasional 
(BRN) separatists in Kabang sub-district was seized by a 
government patrol after a clash yesterday morning. 
  The clash occurred around 7.50 a.m. when the army patrol 
from the Civilian-Police-Military Command 43 under Capt Thara 
Panyachan launched a surprise attack on a hilltop camp near Ban 
Cho Ludi in Tambon Bala. 
  About five bandits, believed to be led by Suwa Khao of the 
BRN, fled the camp after the 20-minute battle. 
  The government force, on the seventh day of its patrol, 
seized five huts and some food. 

