<H3> <TI>   DPRK Reportedly Hiding Nuclear Bombs Underground </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2201010194 Seoul CHOSON ILBO in Korean 22 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK2201010194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] According to a Chinese source on 21 January, North 
Korea has been secretly extracting a considerable amount of 
plutonium while it held nuclear negotiations with the United 
States, and that it is highly possible that North Korea has 
already produced a small nuclear bomb and is hiding it in an 
underground warehouse. This source well-versed in North Korean 
affairs said: "I recently heard from a senior North Korean 
official that North Korea is hiding nuclear weapons in an 
underground warehouse in the mountains near Pyongyang and that 
any thorough inspection of North Korean nuclear facilities [haek 
sisol] by the United States and the International Atomic Energy 
Agency will fail to locate them." 

</TEXT>

