<H3> <TI>   ROK, Japan, Russia To Probe Nuclear Dumping </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2101001894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0008 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2101001894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 21 (YONHAP) -- A joint South Korean, 
Japanese and Russian investigation into possible contamination 
of the East Sea by Russian dumping of nuclear waste is to be 
carried out in late February, informed sources said Thursday. 
  The three countries had planned to hold the investigation in 
mid- January, but had to postpone the plan because of 
differences of opinion over cost sharing, they said. The 
problems were resolved recently. 
  The area for investigation will be the East Sea off 
Hokkaido, 
where the Russian Far-East fleet said it dumped nuclear waste in 
October last year. 

</TEXT>

