<H3> <TI>   President To Reduce Frequency of Interviews </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1801114994 Seoul YONHAP in English 1127 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1801114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Jan. 18 (YONHAP) -- Chongwadae [presidential 
office] has decided to reduce the frequency of the president's 
exclusive interviews with individual press medias on their 
anniversaries. 
  Presidential Press Secretary Chu Ton-sik said on Tuesday 
that 
instead of allowing a presidential interview on every 
anniversary of national and local press medias as now, the 
president will grant an exclusive interview with a media only 
once in three years. 
  "In the past, President Kim Yong-sam gave all anniversary 
interviews requested, which means the president had to give 
about 40 exclusive interviews a year," said Chu, adding that 
when those given to the Chongwadae press corps are taken into 
account, the number rises to about 50. 
  The reduced interviews will not affect President Kim's 
monthly meetings with the Chongwadae press corps, Chu said. 

</TEXT>

