<H3> <TI>   Quality of Pusan Water Restored to `Normalcy' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1501085794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0824 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1501085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pusan, Jan. 15 (YONHAP) -- The Pusan Waterworks 
Agency reported on Saturday that the water quality of its water 
treatment plants has been restored to pre-pollution normalcy. 
  The report said the ammonia and nitrogen content stood at 
0.45ppm in treated water at Toksan water treatment plant and 
0.48ppm at Hwamyong plant, respectively, Saturday morning, below 
the tolerable level of 0.5ppm. 
  A public uproar erupted on Jan. 8 after toxic smell was 
smelt 
and a high content of hazardous substances was detected at 
piped-water in the Pusan area. 
  The waterworks agency also said no more benzene and toluene 
were detected at Mulkum and Maeri water intake yards or in 
piped-water in five separate areas in Pusan on Friday. 

